orm{{\vec x}_1-{\vec x}_4}}s$$ with ${\vec x}_1(0) = (0,0),\  {\vec x}_2(0) = (0,1),\ {\vec x}_3(0) = (1,1),\ {\vec x}_4(0) = (1,0)$. I have noticed that the sum of the gradients is 0, but I don't know if that is helpful or not. Can someone help me figure this problem out?

